íŸ@7a211acdcded292c4f6e063f464aa6caf653ec7e00aaac4060222f9085c347b5⁄˘Title: title: path basename
Path: Examples
Content:
Get basename of a path.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> '/home/joe/test.txt' | path basename
test.txt

```
Get basename of a list of paths.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [ /home/joe, /home/doe ] | path basename
‚ï≠‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ïÆ
‚îÇ 0 ‚îÇ joe ‚îÇ
‚îÇ 1 ‚îÇ doe ‚îÇ
‚ï∞‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¥‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ïØ


```
Replace basename of a path.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> '/home/joe/test.txt' | path basename --replace 'spam.png'
/home/joe/spam.png

```
